 It means memory capacity is increased  and we can put more and more transistors and electrical components inside the chips  The improvement has been dramatic  and that is why we have bigger and bigger memory today  However  the downside of this trend is the circuits are getting smaller and smaller  and therefore they are not as reliable as before at transistor level According to Zhang  we need more protection on top of the Error Correcting Code  ECC  for server memory  such as for scientific or financial computing  MemGuard can enhance the reliability of those computers However  Zhang wants to find a solution that can also work without ECC  The general idea is to design memory integrity checking scheme  if I download a file from the Web  It will check periodically  We only have to change the memory controller in the processor  It is a low cost solution that can work alone without ECC  or work with ECC as an enhancement principal investigator for the three year award  which runs until June           Zhang was originally the principal investigator when he submitted the proposal as a faculty member at Iowa State University before he joined UIC in January      Zhang profile By David Staudacher  UIC David Staudacher  UIC   Facebook    Twitter    Google Plus    Linkedin    Tumblr    Email    You may also like    Engineering Students Win    K Prize at Hackathon       New Engineering Organization Building Electric Car and Opportunities  Previous Professor Devroye is Pushing the Limits of Wireless Communication   Next Professor Stroscio Elected to the AIMBE College of Fellows  UIC Connect Orientations Information for New Students ECE Student Affairs Office       Sciences   Engineering Offices      South Morgan St M C      Chicago  IL             Sciences   Engineering Offices      South Morgan St M C      Chicago  IL                    Future Students Future Students Undergraduate Studies Undergraduate Studies Graduate Studies Graduate Studies Courses Courses Student Organi